website_summaries.verdict: The Woodees earphones feature a unique wooden earpiece enclosure that creates a sound more akin to that of speakers than earbuds. If you like open, natural-sounding audio, be sure to give them a listen.
pros: Woodees Inner Ear Stereo Earphones offer a unique design with earpieces encased in wood rather than plastic or metal
They sound more speaker-like than other earbuds, and several genres of music shine with great audio quality
One version comes with an in-line mic for use with the iPhone or other music phones
cons: The reverberation within the wood sometimes lends a muffled quality to the bass, and not all genres of music sound good

customer_reviews.title: Very cute but not that smart
customer_reviews.text: My experience was pretty close to identical to Cesar's. One of the buds began "crackling" like crazy on the treadmill last night, 11-2/3 months after I got this pair, and the sleeve covering the jack wasn't sealed and would just slide off. The sound was good--better bass than iPod buds, for sure--but I had to adjust them almost constantly to keep them from coming loose while running. I just ordered "Mpow® Swift Bluetooth 4.0 Wireless Stereo Sweatproof Jogger, Running, Sport Headphones Earbuds Earphone with AptX,Mic Hands-free Calling for iphon Sold by: Patozon $29.99" and I'll see how those do.
customer_reviews.author: Goodtherapy

customer_reviews.title: The "wood" makes a real differnece!
customer_reviews.text: The "wood" is NOT a gimmick! The rich, natural tone, smooth bass and frequency response is apparent when contrasted to other earphones. This is my 3rd pair, and the first pair cost about twice the current price. So, a real bargain! I think you should give them a try.
customer_reviews.author: JAY

customer_reviews.title: I was intrigued...
customer_reviews.text: I heard so many good things about wooden ear buds. I own Bose over ear, Monster in ear and Shure in ear already. So I thought I would give these a try. I agree that the quality/resonation of the sound via wood is very pure and warm. However, I simply cannot get these things to seat far enough into my ear to block out any outside noise. Now, for 30 odd dollars I won't complain because I just leave them by my bed, but if I had paid more I would be upset. Anyway, I think they are ok.
customer_reviews.author: BT

customer_reviews.title: Good quality, reasonable sound
customer_reviews.text: My primary concern when buying earbuds was to find a pair that have powerful enough bass and crisp enough treble to make classical, rock, and electronic music sound good. I threw away some much more expensive earbuds because they didn't fit the bill with respect to bass. These fit the bill exactly. The cases are not small, but the sound keeps improving the longer I use them. Sound isolation is reasonable given that they have no active noise canceling technology built in. I've used them on planes, walking to school and in cars, and I've been happy with my purchase.
customer_reviews.author: C. Wiley

customer_reviews.title: nice
customer_reviews.text: I actually ordered these by mistake wanting the model which had a control for volume/phone. But kept them anyway. The price was OK but would not have considered them at the advertised regular price of $60.00. They came with shirt clip, 4 different size ear cushions, comfy, good fit, good sound pass-through.
customer_reviews.author: Cluch

customer_reviews.title: Very Good!
customer_reviews.text: I bought these to replace the pair that came with my iPod. I really like the Woodees. Why? 1) Very comfortable. 2) They don't fall out. 3) Sound quality is very good. Example... I put these in at work and I just get lost in the music. People have to tap me on the shoulder to get my attention I'm enjoying the experioence that much. I would (and have) recommend these to a friend.
customer_reviews.author: Mr. Moto

customer_reviews.title: Best ear buds
customer_reviews.text: Great sounding ear buds, but the quality of the product was a little off and manageable. At the piece that goes into the MP3 player has an issue but it is only cosmetic. The metal that covers the wire tends to come out but you can just glue it back on if that is what you want to do. That is what I did and it is fine. Bass sounds really rich and no distortion! You will like them if you purchase them.
customer_reviews.author: rob

customer_reviews.title: Sound great
customer_reviews.text: I am not a big fan of IEMs but find them convenient for some situations. I do not find any IEMs comfortable so I won't complain about these. I previously had a pair of Westone UM-1s that were better in every way, but I was not willing to pay that kind of money for something I use so seldom. So I am fine with these for my use.
customer_reviews.author: RFC

customer_reviews.title: very comfortable, excellent sound
customer_reviews.text: I've been stung by several pairs of short life earbuds lately (I'm talking to you, Logitech "Ultimate Ears") so I wasn't expecting much in the way of comfort or durability. After a week, I'm impressed with the perceived build quality and the comfort level. Highly recommend for shoppers looking for full immersion in their music with earbuds. Price is also reasonable to my mind.
customer_reviews.author: Miles Baltrusaitis

customer_reviews.title: I really do like the sound but they don't seem to be constructed ...
customer_reviews.text: I bought one pair of these and after having them for about a mouth I noticed one of the small screens missing it really didn't effect the sound but for what I paid I didn't think one should have came out. I decided to buy another pair and the minute I opened them one of the screens fell out of the ear piece. I really do like the sound but they don't seem to be constructed very well.
customer_reviews.author: cappy

customer_reviews.title: Nice item
customer_reviews.text: I really like these earphones. The sound is very good for the money and the fit is excellent. The item was shipped very promptly and packaged protectively. In this case, I got more than my money's worth. They also look great.
customer_reviews.author: scout1968

customer_reviews.title: Wanted to Love Them
customer_reviews.text: I wanted to love these buds, but they now collect dust in the corner of my desk. I though the concept of using wood as an audio chamber was a great idea, but in practice - it's just not. Maybe there's a way to make these sound great, but the current design just doesn't do it. If you're looking for full, rich sound from an ear bud - this is not your product. If you're looking for a conversation piece that never gets plugged into your iPod... then buy away!
customer_reviews.author: Elliott

customer_reviews.title: Best earplugs I've owned
customer_reviews.text: I've gone through multiple earplugs in recent years, and these are by far, the tops for solid, rich sound at this price. The noise canceling is outstanding and I've even just used them as earplugs on flights for when I want to sleep. I recently forgot them on a trip and purchased a cheaper pair at the airport. The difference is enormous. That said, I think there are two draw-backs in my opinion: (a) even though the fit is snug, when I run do other mobile activities, the earplugs fall out occasionally (b) this isn't the worst thing given that the noise canceling probably doesn't make them the safest to wear when running or biking.
customer_reviews.author: harold

customer_reviews.title: Excellet quality and sound
customer_reviews.text: Purchased these for my wife after owning another Woodees earphone that she lost. Highly recommend these! Top quality and sound.
customer_reviews.author: HudsonStudebakerguy

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: was jamming out on them today and still love the warm sound it gives my rock and roll
customer_reviews.author: Thomas A. Overstreet

customer_reviews.title: Sounds good but don't last, and no warranty service.
customer_reviews.text: Sound quality is excellent, but durability is really bad. First pair I bought lost one channel in about 8 months, no response from manufacturer on warranty service. Bought a second one for my daughter, one channel went out after four months, again no response on warranty. Gave up on these, Sennheisers are better and more durable.
customer_reviews.author: James K.T. Wang

customer_reviews.title: Great fit. Great sound
customer_reviews.text: These ear buds are outstanding. They cancel most outside noise and provide a great sound. I like as well as my Bose "noise cancelling" headphones.
customer_reviews.author: thc

customer_reviews.title: the sound was nice, but the construct was poor
customer_reviews.text: Gave up after a year of use, the sound was nice, but the construct was poor. The sleeve that covered the jack slid right off. The adhesive failed.
customer_reviews.author: Cesar

customer_reviews.title: Bought for my son in law
customer_reviews.text: We bought some of these for my son in law and my husband liked them so much we bought some for him.
customer_reviews.author: Joana in Brazil

customer_reviews.title: Save your money
customer_reviews.text: Item was nothing how it was described. I received the item and off rip the left ear bud was already blown out. These are poorly made and I do not recommend them for the price. The bass is not deep as it advertise. The sound quality is clear but that's about it. There are headphones cheaper than these that get the job done efficiently. Save your money
customer_reviews.author: Tim Jones

customer_reviews.title: Great ear buds for a great price
customer_reviews.text: Woodees are unsurpassed in sound quality when compared to other ear buds at this price. So far everything about them is great save for the slight noise made when the cable rubs on clothing. I love these and would recommend them to anyone looking for nice ear buds at a reasonable price.
customer_reviews.author: Tim

customer_reviews.title: GREAT SOUND
customer_reviews.text: So pleasantly surprised by the sound booming from these simple, pretty earbuds. Customized the settings using my cool new Samsung Galaxy S4 sound personalization feature and the audio blew me away. Acoustic guitar strings were incredible. Great value for the price. I plan to buy some as gifts. Try them!
customer_reviews.author: THEGina

customer_reviews.title: Looks nice, but no bass,and fragile
customer_reviews.text: Compared to the normal apple headphones, these have barely any bass. Otherwise the sound is fairly crisp. In terms of quality, I found mine to be very fragile and I am already replacing them since I keep losing sound in the right earbud. (seems to be the Y splitter). I wouldn't buy these again.
customer_reviews.author: Chris

customer_reviews.title: Excellent sound and quality!!!!
customer_reviews.text: All I can say is get them if you want good headphones that don't cost a fortune because they do not get much clearer sounding than these...
customer_reviews.author: Hubby2311

customer_reviews.title: wood sound rocks
customer_reviews.text: As with any musical insturment the tone wood helps produce is amazing. The use of wood in these give is a good clean tone with depth and warmth. Comfortable to wear as well.
customer_reviews.author: J. Cutshall

customer_reviews.title: Thanks
customer_reviews.text: Thanks for the purchase. We are enjoying them. I will be back for more purchases in the future. You Rock!
customer_reviews.author: Rene Aguayo

customer_reviews.title: Excellent bass.  Great custom fit.
customer_reviews.text: The 4 different silicone bud sizes enables you to fit these earbuds perfectly! Great sound (especially the bass tones). Nicely blocks external noises.
customer_reviews.author: MaryEllen Hart

customer_reviews.title: Poor Build Quality
customer_reviews.text: When I purchased these headphones, I was very excited to receive them. Upon taking them out of the box and starting to listen to them, I noticed that when I made even the slightest movement, the audio would scratch/cut out/diminish. Although the sound quality was gorgeous when they WORKED, it didn't really matter. Also, being that they were made out of wood, they were very heavy, cumbersome, and uncomfortable. After 5 minutes of trying to make them work and feeling how uncomfortable they were, I decided to return them. They're manufactured by some off-brand that I have never heard of, so obviously quality control at that company is sub-par. I would most likely steer clear of these.
customer_reviews.author: pennskee89

customer_reviews.title: Excellent sound quality
customer_reviews.text: These woodies iesw101B ear buds offer excellent sound quality at a reasonable cost. They have a natural warm sound and they are comfortable to wear for long periods. Highly recommend.
customer_reviews.author: Michael Cassidy

customer_reviews.title: CLEAR SOUND
customer_reviews.text: THIS IS FOR GUYS WHO LIKES HEAR MUSIC NATURALLY NICE EARPHONE MAKE WITH WOOD PLEASE TRY IT YOU GOING TO ENJOY
customer_reviews.author: jez

customer_reviews.title: Don't buy!!!
customer_reviews.text: I bought these for my son for Christmas 2011. It is now March 2012 and they do not work anymore and I can not return them. Very BAD product, DO NOT waste your money!!!
customer_reviews.author: Doc1352

customer_reviews.title: A classic spin on new technology
customer_reviews.text: Have You ever heard the old saying... there are two types of consumers; Low tech and high tech. Throw out what you think you know with yesterdays garbage, because I'm here to tell ya, these earbuds ROCK! I cannot think from recent memory of when I was so caught by surprise when a product had mixed current technology with organic wood. The sound is amazing, so rich and deep. These even sound better than my $200.00 ear buds. If your looking to replace your tired ol' ipod earbuds, consider giving these babies a once over.
customer_reviews.author: 4EverYoung

customer_reviews.title: Good enough for B, good enough for me.
customer_reviews.text: These headphones don't really deliver the richest, deepest base possible, the sound in my pair tends towards being higher and occasionally sounds a little buzzy (the buzzing seems to have decreased as I've listened to more music with them). I like the rubber tips, they give you a variety of options so you have a reasonable chance of finding a fit you like. I wouldn't recommend this for an audiophile, but I think these are good headphones for most people. I'm certainly satisfied with this product.
customer_reviews.author: A. Christy

customer_reviews.title: Best earphones on the market
customer_reviews.text: Finally earphones that delivery quality bass unlike any other earphones on the market. The choice of earbuds to customize your fit is also a great feature to help capture the quality sound and block out any outside noises. The various sized earbud choices also provide a snug fit so they stay in your ear during activities. These are by far the best earphones i've ever listened to. Brad Riffel
customer_reviews.author: MaggieMay

customer_reviews.title: These look good, sound nice, but have one serious flaw...
customer_reviews.text: To me, it's unimportant how these sound. They have one flaw that prevents me from recommending them. The earphone magnifies the sound of every touch of the cord, movement, yawn, scrape...everything... You loudly hear the slightest wire movement reverberating in your ears. It may be due to the way the wire directly feeds into the transducer (look at the cutaway drawing in the description) or the fact that the wood is acoustically live or the rubbery coating on the wire...it doesn't really matter. You hear noise every time the cord touches anything. It's really too bad. They really look nice. They even sound good. I just wish they weren't completely unwearable. Unless you're a mannequin, look elsewhere.
customer_reviews.author: WB Halper

customer_reviews.title: Really liked them, shorted out quickly
customer_reviews.text: I thought these were really great, even though they're a bit larger than other earbuds. The sound was nice and round. Sadly, they started shorting out within 1-2 months...
customer_reviews.author: Greenzebra

customer_reviews.title: simply the best
customer_reviews.text: Simply the best sounding earbuds I,ve ever heard. I,ve owned many earbuds in my life, these out rank many costing 4x,s as much. I own top of the line in all electronics and very hard to satisfy. I am very satisfied with this product.
customer_reviews.author: Shannon C.

customer_reviews.title: Good option if you're on a budget
customer_reviews.text: I have a pair of full enclosed sennheiser headphones that have better sound quality, but they cost $200. These have great sound quality, especially if you like bass. They're compact, comfortable, and block out most outside noise. I just moved to NYC and they really help quiet the city down. A great value, just not top-of-the-line.
customer_reviews.author: a is a

customer_reviews.title: Great service
customer_reviews.text: I had a problem with these earphones and got in touch with the company. They responded efficiently and appropriately, so I'm all set. And great sound quality as well.
customer_reviews.author: Marc Mauer

customer_reviews.title: amazing sound quality
customer_reviews.text: These are by far THE BEST earphones I've ever used - the sound quality is fantastic and they are super comfortable to wear - plus they stay put even when I'm out running! Great product!
customer_reviews.author: Carly Immen

customer_reviews.title: I love my Woodees
customer_reviews.text: I love my new Woodees. I use them everyday and they sound amazing. I normally dont like earbuds, but these feel great and sound even better. I love them so much I am going to send a pair to my mom for Mother's day.
customer_reviews.author: Gina Gordon

FROM THE MANUFACTURER


PREPARE FOR THE EXPERIENCE OF PURE LISTENING PLEASURE
Like a well-tuned piano or the finest acoustic guitar, Woodees Inner Ear Stereo Earphone with Microphone from iConnects delivers pure listening pleasure. Woodees feature natural wood housing for deep bass performance, full range timbre and noise isolating inner ear fit. 

Solidly constructed, lightweight and ergonomically designed, these stylish natural wood earphones bring out a dense, polished listening experience from your MP3/4 player. And at about half the price of comparable high end earphones, you're getting the best sound at the best price. Give your ears a pair today. 








Natural wood provides superior performance and a sleek look WOOD SOUNDS RICHER 

Natural Wood Housing The most superb musical instruments have always been made from wood because nothing beats its deep bass, rich range of sound and inherent low resonance. We combined the latest high technology design of the transducer (loudspeaker) with the old world splendor of natural wood to create earphones with the perfect balance of performance and value. 

Elegant Design 

Woodees earphones sound gorgeous. Their unique wood housing provides not just a rich range of audio, but fantastic looks too. Gold accents add a touch of class. Woodees' distinct appearance makes them stand out from the crowd. 

Noise Isolating Inner Ear Fit 

Each kit comes with four extra pairs of soft silicone ear buds in extra small, small, medium and large sizes for a customized fit. A more precise fit means less noise coming in from outside to interfere with your music and enhances the Woodees' noise isolating performance, offering listeners a uniquely exceptional audio experience. 




Take a tour through the key features 
of Woodees earphones. Click to learn more Premium Features In addition to their extraordinary look and fit, Woodees are made of quality parts inside and out. 

The cable's soft urethane rubber outer jacket ensures durability, improved flexibility and tangle-free management, and its comfort slide block is adjustable for secure fit. Its multi-strand oxygen-free copper construction ensures the widest frequency response and lowest resistance. 

24K gold connections offer maximum signal transfer and corrosion resistance. 

The high-strength neodymium magnets produce increased sensitivities for distortion-free high volume levels in a compact design. 

Woodees are compatible with smartphones, including the iPhone 2G/3G, iPods and all music devices with a 3.5mm earphone jack. 



What's in the Box 


 * Inner Ear Stereo Earphone 
 * Four pairs of silicone ear buds 
 * Cloth pouch for protection
